          <strong>Course description</strong> <br>
          Software Testing is an approach to assure software quality that is widely adopted in industry. The goal of this course is to introduce Software Testing to students of various backgrounds. The course will cover concepts at different levels. The first two days of the course will cover basic material (e.g., definitions, coverage adequacy, etc.) to students that have no exposure to the discipline. Then, progressively, the course will cover more advanced concepts (e.g., fuzzing, symbolic execution, bounded model checking) and problems investigated in academic research.
